spanGrp.span: ‘I saw that a tiger/a boy was teasing a dog;
Í sũã'-je-nã nãmã pedulagle damĩũ-te kab/ chichi köri-gate
I saw that he was running away from the dog before it.
í sũã'-je-nã í tunã'junã-mĩ chichi tö/ chichi wö tsõ
The dog wanted to corner him.
When trying to escape from the dog, he entered a place where there was a tiger sleeping, a huge tiger,
chichi yiga í pakká mãĩ nãmã kate köpö ska Nãmã tã'ĩ
He could not open the door.
He thought he would go to another house.
Ñerö begesá-ite í mĩ jũ kwãwã mẽ
He suddenly opened the door and there was a tigress that roared at him.
jukö yá-ite plaja ñẽ (m) nãmã alaki kel jeska (_) anã' í wö ñẽ je
He immediately closed the door but hit his head on something, which fell down and he caught him in the air.
kötiá-ite plaja í tsagu kenã' nẽ jirö mẽ je böganãũ-mĩ gugá-ite siwã' inga
The tiger would not wake up;
he did not hear the noise of the steps.
The tiger/that water/at that point the dog came to bite him and it finally did.
Nãmã të/ ñẽ diglö/ je jueta chichi beteũ í kwö chichi të í kwá
I saw there was a woman coming and she suddenly got scared,
jemẽ í sũã'-je-ra-nã alaglöwa dajũ jejueta kinã'-wã yessö nã
“Who says that humans live with tigers?”
“¿yurö të í she-nã' sersö rö sẽr ta nãmã ra jũ jãrga“
Then she fainted at once and fell down.
Ñerö í wö nã í damãũ plaja egweta í janã-mĩ ekka_uña í tsagu wötöwinã' janã-mĩ
When she woke up, he didn’t/she realized that he/she had been sleeping;
je shkinã-ra ka í wak/ ksá-ite-ra-nã í köpö blali
he called and said to her that the tiger would not do anything to me, I am tiger, the family.
í kiá-ite-ra shá-ite-nã „nãmã ka të yís mẽwanã Yís (_) rö (_) nãmã je yaiwa bö“
He showed the tiger his hand,, but the tiger showed him his teeth
Nãmã (_) wö nã da í jula kashö ñẽ nãmã ka jatká í wö nã
Je të í tuwã' plaja (_) je të í je mẽnẽũ-mĩ tör köũ
The woman closed the door on the tiger;
alaglöwa të jũkö mwã'-wã nãmã yiga
he climbed onto a light pole all the way to the top
Je mẽnẽũ lus sei kel je klögata je klö mẽ mẽnẽũ (_) í de-gãũ í bata ska
and showed her his hand as if mockering;
Jeska í jula kashö-gẽ bius_bius ba wö na
he came down; there it was cut and ended.’
jẽk (_) jawã-te jeska í onã' tenã
